caption: A beautifully quiet and secluded garden in memory of Anne Frank.  We stopped by to eat some baguettes we had purchased from a local bakery and soak in the atmosphere.  There are plenty of benches to sit and relax and a table tennis table.  We did also see a children's playground but it was fenced off, I presume as they were doing some maintenance work.  The blossoms were out and its a great place to enjoy a quiet picnic lunch or chat with friends.

A beautiful and a bit hidden in the Le Marais area unless you explore it. Now it‚Äôs the peak time for the roses are blooming, so beautiful. But the public toilet tho, NEED a immediate help and rescue. Eww.
Good park for the kids with plenty of benches in the shade.

In the heart of Marais, the entrance to the garden is one you can miss easily as it essentially is off an alley.  The initial garden is quaint and as you walk in further, you will see the rest of the larger garden, trellis and hear children playing.  Placards with information about this incredible young lady are near the entrance.  If nearby, is worth walking to and spending a bit of time to take a break and reflect.
Cute little pocket park. They close around 8pm
Peaceful and calm hidden square where I had an impromptu picnic. Everything I wanted was purchased at Le Cul de Cochon.
A beautiful secret garden in the Marais
Calm and green. Playground for the kids but space to relax for the adults. Flowers and a public WC. Perfect escape (ironic) in the Marais.
Peaceful garden with a small childrens park. Peaceful and respectful.

Nice, peaceful place. Tucked away. Outdoor table tennis and chess available (bring your own bits.) come l sculpture there too (see pic). There's a chestnut tree grown from a tree from Anne Frank's garden.
A lovely quiet, hidden away park off the busy Paris streets with an important message for all.
Calme and very cool. There's a place to sit down or lay down. Some trees and cool wooden pergole.

A hidden garden in Le Marais, a tribute to Anne Frank, known for her WWII diary. This oasis is brimming with history. In fact, it are 3 different gardens, with their own character. Let me take you there virtually...  Follow me for more Insider's info of a local in Paris  #JardinAnneFrank #Paris #Paris2024
Cute little park. Nice, quiet and secluded - the perfect place for a little morning pastry and coffee.
Peaceful and secluded park hidden in a bustling Paris neighbourhood.
Nice, kind of hidden park in the middle of Paris with a playground for children.
This parc is located centrally in Paris. However, due to the somewhat hidden entrance it is always very calm and you can easily find a place to enjoy the sun. See picture for the view from above.
A great park to never forget Anne Frank. Rest in peace...

A cool hidden place near pompadour, it has a lot of rats but they don't bother anyone The play ground is cool and has a lot of things for kids There's also a water fountain ‚õ≤ The one and only entrance is completely hidden between buildings, there is always a place all week contrary to pompadour
Hidden away near the Pompidou Centre a secluded garden with covered walks and beautiful trees. Two wooden sculptures grace the entrance.
Very nice and clean garden.  There is a playground inside.
What a peaceful stunning garden to take a break and relax!
Delightful urban oasis, great place to decompress
My favorite garden in Paris. Nice and quiet in the middle of town

This is definitely a new favourite spot. Hidden place in le Marais and its a great spot to sit to eat your lunch. When I went, there wasn't that many people which is nice because it was a nice way to escape from the crowds. Would definitely recommend as a spot to go for a break

Great enclosed garden, hidden between houses. Great to come for a game of chess (bring your pieces, checkerboard are painted on the tables), for children to play, or simply to read: you will not hear the noise from the rest of Paris.

A calm place where you can go I'm the middle of Paris, with playground for kids and water tap to drink and fill your bottles, not to mention the meaning of the garden.
Looks cute but it was closed when I came by on the morning of May 10th

Nice relaxing garden created as a homage to Anne Frank. We took our 11 year old daughter there after she read her biography. Worth a visit if you have kids and are in the area. Also important to know Anne's story for today's modern generations.

Beautiful hidden place to enjoy of some peace in the middle of the city. Great for families with kids, for yiug people or for ealderly adults who want to enjoy beautiful architecture, peace, quietness and nature.
Lovely, quiet, little park with 3 separate areas and a great little playground. Lots of benches and grass to sit on! Great place for a picnic.

It feels a little tucked away and quiet.  Little kids Park.  There were moments where it didn't feel as though it was frequented by the most charming of folks but there was a security guard doinh his rounds frequently
Well. It is not quiet at all. Noisy. Full of kids. No flower in October. Hope to see more about Anne-Frank here.
Lovelly small park with a good children's play area and seating. Could have small picnic tables as many like us having lunch
